# React and TypeScript

- Use functional components only.
- Type props explicitly; use `React.FC<Props>` when it improves readability.
- Custom hooks live in `src/hooks/` and use the `use` prefix.
- Prefer `memo()` for presentational list items when props are stable.
- Avoid `any`; use `unknown` and narrow, or proper generics.
